- `src/seccomp-bpf.c` -- BPF filter generation\n- `src/fd-table.c` -- virtual FD table (two-range: low 0..1023, high 32768+)\n- `src/shadow-fd.c` -- memfd shadows for O_RDONLY files (enables mmap)\n- `src/path.c` -- path normalization and virtual/host routing\n- `src/elf.c` -- ELF parser, PT_INTERP extraction\n- `src/mount.c` -- mount profiles (raw, recommended, standard)\n- `include/kbox/lkl-wrap.h` -- LKL stat struct and ABI translation\n\n### Critical ABI rules\n- LKL uses asm-generic stat (128 bytes). Host x86_64 stat is 144 bytes.\n  Always use `struct kbox_lkl_stat` + `kbox_lkl_stat_to_host()`.\n- seccomp args[] zero-extend 32-bit values. Use `to_dirfd_arg()` for sign extension.\n- aarch64 O_* flags differ from asm-generic. Translate bidirectionally.\n\n### FD table design\n- `KBOX_FD_BASE=32768` splits virtual FDs into two ranges\n- `entries[]` for FDs >= 32768 (normal allocation)\n- `low_fds[1024]` for FDs 0..1023 (only via dup2/dup3)\n- Gap [1024, 32768) is untracked (documented limitation)\n\n### BPF filter\n- `close` is NOT in the allow list (goes through USER_NOTIF -> forward_close)\n- `sendmsg` IS in the allow list (child pre-exec SCM_RIGHTS)\n\n## Review Workflow\nImplement -> self-review -> Gemini + Codex MCP (parallel) -> consensus fixes -> rebuild + retest.\n",
